@startuml
' @id(USE-AGENT-PREPARE)
' @desc(USE-AGENT-PREPARE, "`mdd agent --kind <cursor|codex|claude|generic>` prepares a coding agent's MDD working context from the CLI. Until now mdd-agent::prepare_agent had no caller; this use case wires it behind a real subcommand. The arm discovers the Project and calls mdd_agent::prepare_agent(&project, kind), which writes .mdd/docs/<agent>-mdd.md instruction file and runs any executable .mdd/hooks/pre-code* hooks in sorted order, failing fast on a non-zero hook. It prints the instruction file written and the hooks run. Realized by SEQ-AGENT-PREPARE; owned by CMP-AGENT-PREPARE over DOM-AGENT-PREP.")
title MDD agent prepare CLI — wire mdd-agent behind a subcommand (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev

rectangle "mdd toolchain" {
  usecase "Prepare an agent's MDD context\n(mdd agent --kind <agent>)" as AgentPrepare
}

Dev --> AgentPrepare

note bottom of AgentPrepare
  Objective (USE-AGENT-PREPARE): Commands::Agent { kind } ->
  mdd_agent::prepare_agent(). Writes .mdd/docs/<agent>-mdd.md
  and runs .mdd/hooks/pre-code* in order. Local dev tooling;
  no auth/crypto surface (fixed command, kind is an enum).
end note
@enduml
